alysis and detailed histories of immigrants in addition to the perspectives of officials, this richly illustrated book traces how visual regulations became central in the early development of U.S. immigration policy and in the introduction of racial immigration restrictions. In so doing, it provides the historical context for understanding more recent developments in immigration policy and, at the same time, sheds new light on the cultural history of American photography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEthnicityxPolitical aspectszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aIdentification photographszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aImmigrantsxHealth and hygienezUnited StatesxHistory. 0aImmigrantszUnited StatesxIdentificationxHistory. 0aPortrait photographyxPolitical aspectszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  aamerican photography.  aamerican studies.  aangel island.  aasian american history.  achinese exclusion act.  achinese immigrants.  adiaspora.  aellis island.  aethnography.  aeuropean immigrants.  ahealth.  ahistory.  aimmigrants.  aimmigration policy.  aimmigration.  ainspections.  alewis hine.  amexico border.  amigrant workers.  amigration.  anonfiction.  apassing.  apassports.  aphotography.  apolitics.  arace.  aracial immigration restrictions.  arefugees.  aregulations.  aunited states history.  avisual culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025298140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520944633?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944633423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944633/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 20